For generating conroller with name pages
rails generate controller Pages

2)For running test cases in spec folder using rspec
rspec spec/

3)For generating a model with fields
rails generate model User name:string email:string



#Active Record commands
1) For creating new object 
User.new(with parameter)

2)For saving created object
User.save

3)For directly creating and saving object
User.create(with parameters)

4)For updating any attribute.After setting the attribute in the first way we need to call user.save. Otherwise it wont reflect in database.
user.parameter="blah blah"
user.save
       (or)
user.update_attributes(paramters hash to update)

5)After setting the parameter if you want to reset to actual object with values in database u need to call
user.reload.parameter



 
